<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,972,1460]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,546,1116,1141]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Distribution in North 
<collectingCountry box="[466,541,1116,1141]" name="China" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">China</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
Only on the edge of the east Qinghai-Tibetan plateau in Gansu. Abundant at medium to high elevations of the Qilianshan nature reserve in Tianzhu, common at medium elevatons of the Liancheng nature reserve in Yongdeng, and rare at high elevations of the Zhagana nature reserve in Diebu. 
<number box="[1409,1436,1189,1213]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" value="11.0">11</number>
localities (
<figureCitation box="[267,363,1224,1249]" captionStart="FIGURES 136 – 137. 136" captionStartId="67.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,1502,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@67.[155,1440,1502,1928]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURES 136 – 137. 136. Map showing the distribution of B. validus in North China with records as black spots, the province boundaries in dark grey, and all sites with records of all bumblebee species in light grey. 137. B. validus worker visiting Ligularia sp. (Asteraceae) in Gansu." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286627/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Fig. 
<number box="[320,363,1224,1249]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" value="136.0">136</number>
</figureCitation>
) between 
<quantity box="[478,633,1224,1249]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.86" metricValueMax="3.5239999999999996" metricValueMin="2.196" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" unit="m" value="2860.0" valueMax="3524.0" valueMin="2196.0">2196–3524 m</quantity>
(IAB).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,972,1460]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,589,1260,1285]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Similar species in North 
<collectingCountry box="[516,589,1260,1285]" name="China" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">China</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
